Cameroon legend and former Chelsea player, Geremi, has cautioned Nigeria’s Super Eagles to be wary of Egypt’s Mohamed Elneny in their opening match of AFCON 2021 in Cameroon Egypt will start its journey tomorrow against Nigeria at the Roumde Adjia Stadium in Garoua. The Pharaohs are led by Liverpool superstar Mohamed Salah, who will be joined by other Premier League players in Mahmoud Trezeguet of Aston Villa and Arsenal’s Mohamed Elneny.   AFCON opens in flash of colour amid Covid-19     AFN unveils programmes, names sub-committee heads     Osimhen clears of COVID-19   Despite his lack of playing time with the Gunners, Elneny has always been a consistent performer with the national team and Geremi believes this AFCON won’t be any different. “Mohamed Elneny is also a standout for Egypt, he is an experienced player at the top level and always consistent for Arsenal when he gets the chance to play – and just as important as Mo Salah is for Egypt,” Geremi told Metro.co.uk when asked which players he expects to shine during the tournament. - Advertisement - Elneny made only ten appearances with Arsenal since the start of the season, three of which were in the EFL Cup where he helped his team reach the semi-finals. Due to his limited playtime, Elneny started to appear on other clubs’ radars, especially since his contract ended by the end of the season, with Newcastle United reportedly keen on acquiring his services.